ss.org/changeset/42259), which was part of [the 4.9.1 release](https://wordpress.org/news/2017/11/wordpress-4-9-1-security-and-maintenance-release/).\n","can_view?":true,"can_edit?":false,"content_html":"\u003cp\u003eThe \u003ccode\u003elanguage_attributes()\u003c/code\u003e function was not escaping output, which could lead to an XSS vulnerability if combined with other vulnerabilities.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eTo fix that, the output was \u003ca href=\"/redirect?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcore.trac.wordpress.org%2Fchangeset%2F42259\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003epassed through \u003ccode\u003eesc_attr()\u003c/code\u003e in r42259\u003c/span\u003e\u003ci class=\"icon-external-link\"\u003e\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/a\u003e, which was part of \u003ca href=\"/redirect?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwordpress.org%2Fnews%2F2017%2F11%2Fwordpress-4-9-1-security-and-maintenance-release%2F\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003ethe 4.9.1 release\u003c/span\u003e\u003ci class=\"icon-external-link\"\u003e\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n"},{"category":"researcher","can_view?":true,"can_create?":false}]}